race.comment: GLOBAL ECLIPSE (1) has been in the placings at both runs this prep, most recently a closing second over 1600m at Pakenham. Has a handy 3kg claim and is a strong winning chance. LA ROSETTA (12) peaks and made good improvement last start over 1600m at Moe. The extra metres are ideal, and she has plenty to give. It's hard to risk the barn. ZEACTION (3) resumes further improved with a big Maiden win at Pakenham, heavily supported. This is tougher, but he's showing plenty of promise. MADAME LEXIS (9) is third-up and should be ready to show her best. Has been freshened and kept up to the mark with a jumpout. In the mix with the 2kg claimer on. RED FEATHERS (14) would be around the mark measured on the Mornington Maiden win two back.
